White was 45 when the 48th over started, and he finishes on 89. He blasted 70 of his final 24 balls. At one stage, there were questions over whether Australia would reach 250, they ended up on 289. Last five overs cost India 84 runs. White's hitting has overshadowed what was a well-paced, determined innings from Clarke, who ends unbeaten on 111. He and Hussey steadied Australia with a 144-run stand after the openers fell cheaply, before White left India facing a tough target.

A plethora of exclamation marks from Paras: "Speechless. At first I thought that maybe Aussies would reach 250-260. But Cameron White had other ideas. Hope Yuvi plays a blinder today!!!!"

Kunal David: "What an innings, a game changer!"

Billy is a satisfied Australian fan: "I think that display just proved Australia's dominance in the ODI format. Imagine if Warner and Watson, what should be our first choice opening pair, were at the top of the order..."

Jason points out: "There were only 9 dot balls in the last 10 overs. First rule of batting is to keep the scoreboard ticking over!"

There is some support (and plenty of unflattering feedback) for Vinay Kumar, after the hammering he received today. Ravi says: "Vinay Kumar should still be persisted after today's pasting as Vinay has got the potential to be the next Javagal Srinath for India,lets hope this will be a good learning curve."

And there are plenty of people questioning why Vinay was given the final over.

White's hitting has also stopped all mails about the new Indian jersey. India may have got off to a good start, but it is Australia who have ended their innings on a high. Here's a look back in our Gallery.

6.25pm: Still 20 minutes to go for the chase to start. Time enough for you to check out our free Chrome extension.

And if you missed any of the action, here's Sriram Veera's bulletin to take you through everything that's happened so far.

Annoyed your comment wasn't published during the ball-by-ball commentary. Let the world know what you have to say on our Facebook page.
